    <stitle>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM ANCHORLOK SPRING BRAKE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s04019" svcsectype="prodspec" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5074" date="03/31/1996">
        <title>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM ANCHORLOK SPRING BRAKE</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>ANCHORLOK</vendor>
                <vendor>GOLD SEAL</vendor>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>8100</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8300</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>The Gold Seal Anchorlok double diaphragm spring brake assembly is used as a spring applied parking
                brake and an emergency brake in case of air pressure loss. The assembly is available for both "S" cam
                type and "Wedge" type brakes.
            </para>
            <para>The brake chamber assembly consists of two separate air chambers: the spring brake chamber and the
                service brake chamber (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401901">Figure 1</hotlnk>); each having its own diaphragm and push rod (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401902">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0401901" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0401901" filename="../figg04/G0401901.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Double Diaphragm Spring Brake</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PERMANENTLY SEALED CHAMBER-NO SAFETY EARS OR CLAMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPRING BRAKE CHAMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SERVICE BRAKE CHAMBER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0401902" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0401902" filename="../figg04/G0401902.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Normal Driving Mode</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. POWER SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPRING BRAKE DIAPHRAGM</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SERVICE BRAKE DIAPHRAGM</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.SERVICE BRAKE PUSH ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.SPRING BRAKE PUSH ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.AIR PRESSURE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The difference in the two chambers are:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>The service brake chamber applies the brake by air pressure and releases it by the force of a
                        spring.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>The spring brake chamber applies the brake by spring force and releases it by air pressure.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The spring brake chamber is a permanently sealed chamber that cannot be serviced (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0401901">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
